main event: Two unidentified objects were sighted in the sky over Spokane, Washington.
interesting points: The first object was round and bluish-white in color, changing to greenish-tiny.
The second object was oblong, changing to round, and was brilliant green, silver, and blue in color.
The second object appeared to be spinning very rapidly clockwise when viewed through a 60-power scope.
The objects oscillated like a pendulum and moved slowly to the south and west.
The sighting was reported to the Spokane Police Department, and a major from the 230th Fighter Interceptor Squadron at Fairchild AFB was also a witness.
sighted objects: a round, bluish-white object that changed to greenish-tiny
an oblong, changing to round object that was brilliant green, silver, and blue
witnesses: a civilian patrolman from the Spokane Police Department
a major from the 230th Fighter Interceptor Squadron at Fairchild AFB
